1
Scenario
Assume that you are just hired by a company as a cybersecurity analyst. Your
responsibility is to constantly monitor the hosts in company’s network for malicious
behaviors from intruders. Your new job has a trial period. Your boss, the Chief Security
Officer (CSO) assigns you three tasks below in your trial period. Please complete the
three tasks to keep your position in the company.
Task 1:
Your boss thinks that the Windows hosts in the company have abnormal behaviors. You
are asked to monitor the services running on the company’s Windows hosts.
1.1 Write a PowerShell script (task11.ps1) to automatically display the names of the
services that are running on a machine. Please submit the program and show your
results here.
1.2 Write a Python program (task12.py) to compare the names of the services from 1.1
against a blacklist of malicious programs. Please create the blacklist yourself. The
blacklist can be hypothetical. Please submit the program and show your results here.
In your submission, please include any files that are needed to run your program.
1.3 Describe the process how you use the programs from 1.1 and 1.2 daily to monitor the
services of Windows hosts. The description must be specific enough so that another
specialist can perform the task based on your instructions.
Task 2:
To solve the problem that your boss identified in task 1, you come up with another
solution, that is, using a port scanner to identify malicious services.
2.1 Write a Python program (task21.py) to trigger a port scanner to scan all of the TCP
and UDP ports on a Windows computer in your computer. Try the program on your
localhost to proof that it works. Please submit the program and show your results
here.
2.2 Describe the process how you use the programs from 2.1 daily to monitor the services
of Windows hosts. The description must be specific enough so that another specialist
can perform the task based on your instructions.
2.3 Compare your results from 2.1 with results from task 1. Which method is better for
identifying malicious services on your Windows hosts? Please write at least a half
page response that will be given to your boss in comparing the pros and cons of each
method.
2
Task 3
Your boss also worries about data integrity and scripting security of the programs that
you created in task 1 and task 2. You will need to find solutions to address his concern.
3.1 Please provide a PowerShell script (task31.ps1) to check the data integrity of the
programs in task 1 and task 2.
3.2 Justify and show how can task31.ps1 ensure the data integrity of the programs and
what data integrity really means in this case.
3.3 To ensure scripting security, you decide to digitally sign your PowerShell script.
Please provide a PowerShell script (task33.ps1) to digitally sign task11.ps1. In your
submission, please include the signed version of task11.ps1 (named task11signed.ps1)
3.4 Justify and show why task33.ps1 can ensure the scripting security of PowerShell
programs.
